Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pop the @sweet potato{200%g}(diced) onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{16-18%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Pour the boiled water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}) and cut the @lime{1/2}(cut into wedges). Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a sieve.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour.

Transfer the sweetcorn to a #small bowl{}, then mix in the coriander and @olive oil{for the salsa}. Season with salt and pepper, stir together and set your salsa aside.

> See pantry for amount of olive oil.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%400g can} in a sieve.

Pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the beans, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @chipotle paste{20%g}, @tomato passata{1/2%bottle}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce. Season with salt and pepper.

> See pantry for amounts of sugar and water.

Lightly crush half of the beans in the pan using a #potato masher{}, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the sweet potato has roasted, stir it through the beans with a squeeze of lime juice. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} into your corn salsa.

Squeeze in some lime juice and gently mix through.

Fluff up your rice with a #fork{} and share between your bowls.

Spoon over the chipotle sweet potato and black beans.

Top with the corn and cheese salsa. Finish with any remaining lime wedges. Enjoy!